\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 1}{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 . }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 Each Request for Administration must be accompanied by the non-refundable amount specified in Article 3 of Appendix II. This amoun
t will be credited to the requesting party's or parties' portion of the deposit pursuant to Article 14(3).
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 2}{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 . }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 When the Centre is requested to administer expertise proceedings where the expert has already been proposed or appointed by the Centre in connect
ion with the same matter, the non-refundable amount specified in Article 3 of Appendix II shall not be paid in addition to the non-refundable amounts paid for the proposal or the appointment of an expert and specified in Articles 1 and 2 of Appendix II.

\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 3}{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 . }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 
Following the receipt of a Request for Administration the Centre shall request the parties to pay a deposit in an amount likely to cover the administrative costs of the Centre and the fees and expenses of the expert for the expertise proceedings, as set 
out in Article 3, paragraphs (2) and (3), of Appendix II. The expertise proceedings shall not go forward until payment of such deposit has been received by the Centre.
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 4}{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 . }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 In any case where the Centre considers that the deposit is not likely to cover the t
otal costs of the expertise proceedings, the amount of such deposit may be subject to readjustment. When the request for the corresponding payments has not been complied with, the Centre may suspend the expertise proceedings and set a time limit, on the e
xpiry of which the expertise proceedings may be considered withdrawn.
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 5}{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 . }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 Upon termination of administered expertise proceedings, the Cen
tre shall settle the total costs of the proceedings and shall, as the case may be, reimburse the party or parties for any excess payment or bill the party or parties for any balance required pursuant to these Rules. The balance, if any, shall be payable b
efore the notification of the final expert's report to the party or parties.
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 6}{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 . }{\f1\fs20\insrsid871004\charrsid871004 
All above deposits and costs shall be borne in equal shares by the parties, unless they agree otherwise in writing. However, any party shall be free to pay the unpaid balance o
f such deposits and costs should the other party or parties fail to pay its or their share.
\par }{\f1\fs20\insrsid14166817 
